rounds.response:
I’ve got two X’s in the top row already, so at [1] [0 | 1 | 2] only cells [3], [5], [6], and [8] remain.

A quick scan:

- Center column: needs [5] to win (X at [2] isn’t possible—no X there).  
- Diagonal from top-left to bottom-right: needs [8], but we’d need [4]—don’t have it.  
- Top row already has two X’s, so no winning move there now.  
- Left column has an X at [0]; adding [3] and [6] would only get to three X’s total, not a win outright here.

The only two-move threat I see is grabbing [5]: then if Player 0 tries to stop the center column by playing [5] themselves, I could still get [8] to finish the other diagonal. But right now, [5] alone threatens the immediate center-column win.

So I’ll take [5].
